{
  "stem": "9899.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember that we were to do-- one day we were very late coming back.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were-- we had to run, because otherwise we would be shot.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So my mother-- and we were small children, and she had to carry the baby.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we had to run, and people-- non-Jews would yell, there go the Jews, the Jews, the Jews.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if a German would have seen us, he would have certainly shot us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The anti-Semitism was growing by leaps and bounds, because now there was no one from the Jewish community that could defend us.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The world was standing still.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was absolutely no reaction from any other power or any other country that would inquire after us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We were lost in a maze of terror.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we were sport to whoever wanted to harm us, and no one would lift a finger.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So fear came in to the Jews, and glory and power visited the Gentiles.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So they became strong, and they would harass us and go after us constantly without any measure and without any ending to it.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And soon my father got very sick.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And even though he was ill and not feeling well, he was taken to the labor camps of [?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Janowska. ?] And over there, one day he had to-- his job was to go to the cemetery and take out all the stones, the marbles, of the people that had died so the Germans could pave the streets for their tanks to have a better way of entering.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Because in Poland, and in mainly in-- in-- in Europe, the streets were made of stones, and that was not very comfortable for the big trucks that came.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So they made [INAUDIBLE]-- [BACKGROUND NOISE]",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They forced them to do that.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
